post_text:
We would love to take a moment and recognize an amazing accomplishment of one our wonderful teachers!! Congratulations Mrs. Bagley!! We are so very happy for you and very proud of you!!

"The VFW and Auxiliary Of Athens celebrated the announcement and celebration of Teacher of the Year at the Michigan Mid Winter Conference at the Radisson in Kalamazoo. Teacher, Stacia Bagley was awarded First place for JR High selection. Being honored with a jacket, placque, and $500 monetary gift. Her husband, Seth, accompanied her at the dinner. The VFW and Auxiliary of Athens will attend another recognition program in March in her honor with more awards! She now advances to National competition. Good luck Mrs Bagley. We are proud to have you honored in our organization!"
-Debbie Brand, President and members Members VFW Auxiliary, Athens

***All questions will go through this Athens Area PTSO page or you can call/text 269-967-1369***

Parent/teacher conferences are next week! (10/23& 10/24) The PTSO always provides a meal for the teachers and staff, so we are looking for some volunteers if you're interested in helping out for Wednesday, Oct 23rd. We will be providing pizza this year (voted on at our last meeting). Please let us know what you'd be willing to bring in so we can provide a great meal on such a busy evening. Any food, side dishes/salads, desserts, waters/drinks, etc. would be greatly appreciated. You can respond to this post or message me and I'll put you down. We usually plan for about 25 and items can be dropped off to the school that day or can be arranged for me to pick up if needed. Thank you so much for your help and continued support!

FALL FUN FAIR is TODAY at East Leroy Elementary school from 5-7 pm!! THANK YOU to everyone who sent in their RSVPs!! Your tickets will be ready for you at the door and your wait will be short. If you did not RSVP, no worries!! Still join us and buy your tickets at the door!! Tickets are $0.50/each or 50 tickets for $20!!

**Any questions, please let us know!! PLEASE share, like or ‚ù§ this post or comment with a üéÉ if you see this post!!

All games will cost 1-2 tickets per game. We will have face painting and a little take home art project that will be 2 tickets each.

Tickets or cash may be used to vote for the "Decorate your classroom door contest". The classroom with the most votes/money will win a pizza party!! Voting with cash will also be on Halloween during the classroom parties!!

Food, drinks and snacks will be available for cash purchases only. Tickets may not be used to purchase food.

post_text: Track and Field day is quickly approaching!
